{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["56-TIT-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "TIT"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Titus \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["Paul\u2019s Letter to Titus \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Titus \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Tit \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Paul\u2019s Letter to Titus \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "TIT 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "TIT 1:1"}, "Paul, a servant of Allah, and an apostle of Al Masih Isa, according to the faith of Allah\u2019s chosen ones, and the knowledge\nof the truth which is according to godliness, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "TIT 1:2"}, "in hope of eternal life, which Allah, who can\u2019t lie, promised before time began;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "TIT 1:3"}, "but in his own time revealed his word in the message with which I was entrusted according to the commandment of Allah our\nSaviour; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "TIT 1:4"}, "to Titus, my true child according to a common faith: Grace, mercy, and peace from Allah the Father and the Lord Al Masih\nIsa our Saviour. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "TIT 1:5"}, "I left you in Crete for this reason, that you would set in order the things that were lacking and appoint elders in every\ncity, as I directed you, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "TIT 1:6"}, "if anyone is blameless, the husband of one wife, having children who believe, who are not accused of loose or unruly\nbehaviour. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "TIT 1:7"}, "For the overseer must be blameless, as Allah\u2019s steward, not self-pleasing, not easily angered, not given to wine, not\nviolent, not greedy for dishonest gain; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "TIT 1:8"}, "but given to hospitality, a lover of good, sober minded, fair, holy, self-controlled,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "TIT 1:9"}, "holding to the faithful word which is according to the teaching, that he may be able to exhort in the sound doctrine, and\nto convict those who contradict him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "TIT 1:10"}, "For there are also many unruly men, vain talkers and deceivers, especially those of the circumcision,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "TIT 1:11"}, "whose mouths must be stopped: men who overthrow whole houses, teaching things which they ought not, for dishonest gain\u2019s\nsake. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "TIT 1:12"}, "One of them, a prophet of their own, said, \u201cCretans are always liars, evil beasts, and idle gluttons.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "TIT 1:13"}, "This testimony is true. For this cause, reprove them sharply, that they may be sound in the faith,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "TIT 1:14"}, "not paying attention to Jewish fables and commandments of men who turn away from the truth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "TIT 1:15"}, "To the pure, all things are pure; but to those who are defiled and unbelieving, nothing is pure; but both their mind and\ntheir conscience are defiled. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "TIT 1:16"}, "They profess that they know Allah, but by their deeds they deny him, being abominable, disobedient, and unfit for any\ngood work. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "TIT 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "TIT 2:1"}, "But say the things which fit sound doctrine, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "TIT 2:2"}, "that older men should be temperate, sensible, sober minded, sound in faith, in love, and in perseverance:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "TIT 2:3"}, "and that older women likewise be reverent in behaviour, not slanderers nor enslaved to much wine, teachers of that which\nis good, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "TIT 2:4"}, "that they may train the young wives to love their husbands, to love their children,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "TIT 2:5"}, "to be sober minded, chaste, workers at home, kind, being in subjection to their own husbands, that Allah\u2019s word may not be\nblasphemed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "TIT 2:6"}, "Likewise, exhort the younger men to be sober minded. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "TIT 2:7"}, "In all things be showing yourself an example of good works. In your teaching, be showing integrity, seriousness,\nincorruptibility, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "TIT 2:8"}, "and soundness of speech that can\u2019t be condemned, that he who opposes you may be ashamed, having no evil thing to say about\nus. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "TIT 2:9"}, "Exhort servants to be in subjection to their own masters and to be well-pleasing in all things, not contradicting,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "TIT 2:10"}, "not stealing, but showing all good fidelity, that they may adorn the doctrine of Allah, our Saviour, in all things.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "TIT 2:11"}, "For the grace of Allah has appeared, bringing salvation to all men,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "TIT 2:12"}, "instructing us to the intent that, denying ungodliness and worldly lusts, we would live soberly, righteously, and godly\nin this present age; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "TIT 2:13"}, "looking for the blessed hope and appearing of the glory of our great Allah and Saviour, Al Masih Isa,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "TIT 2:14"}, "who gave himself for us, that he might redeem us from all iniquity, and purify for himself a people for his own\npossession, zealous for good works. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "TIT 2:15"}, "Say these things and exhort and reprove with all authority. Let no one despise you.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "TIT 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "TIT 3:1"}, "Remind them to be in subjection to rulers and to authorities, to be obedient, to be ready for every good work,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "TIT 3:2"}, "to speak evil of no one, not to be contentious, to be gentle, showing all humility towards all men.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "TIT 3:3"}, "For we were also once foolish, disobedient, deceived, serving various lusts and pleasures, living in malice and envy,\nhateful, and hating one another. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "TIT 3:4"}, "But when the kindness of Allah our Saviour and his love towards mankind appeared,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "TIT 3:5"}, "not by works of righteousness which we did ourselves, but according to his mercy, he saved us through the washing of\nregeneration and renewing by the Holy Spirit, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "TIT 3:6"}, "whom he poured out on us richly, through Al Masih Isa our Saviour;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "TIT 3:7"}, "that being justified by his grace, we might be made heirs according to the hope of eternal life.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "TIT 3:8"}, "This saying is faithful, and concerning these things I desire that you affirm confidently, so that those who have believed\nAllah may be careful to maintain good works. These things are good and profitable to men;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "TIT 3:9"}, "but shun foolish questionings, genealogies, strife, and disputes about the law; for they are unprofitable and vain.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "TIT 3:10"}, "Avoid a factious man after a first and second warning, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "TIT 3:11"}, "knowing that such a one is perverted and sins, being self-condemned.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "TIT 3:12"}, "When I send Artemas to you, or Tychicus, be diligent to come to me to Nicopolis, for I have determined to winter there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "TIT 3:13"}, "Send Zenas, the lawyer, and Apollos on their journey speedily, that nothing may be lacking for them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "TIT 3:14"}, "Let our people also learn to maintain good works for necessary uses, that they may not be unfruitful.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "TIT 3:15"}, "All who are with me greet you. Greet those who love us in faith. Grace be with you all. Amen.\n"]}]}